name: Gamer's Guide to Pretty Much Everything
original_name: Gamer's Guide to Pretty Much Everything
overview: Follows professional teenage video gamer, Conor, who is forced to go to high school for the first time, after a thumb injury. Coping with his new lifestyle, he focuses on friendships and visualizes life as a video game.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Conor and Ashley recruit an NBA Player to be their ringer for a charity basketball game, and Wendell attempts to boost the popularity of his "Rekt" videos.

episodes.name: Gamer's Guide to Pretty Much Everything
episodes.overview: Conor wants to get his pro card back, so he recruits new classmates Franklin, Wendell and Ashley to play the game for him. But, a failed attempt to ditch school early to practice lands them in detention with a tough teacher.

episodes.name: The Gaming Club
episodes.overview: The gang forms a gaming club that gets them out of gym class. Wendell goes to great lengths to sneak into the library to return a book he borrowed in the first grade.

episodes.name: The Puddin Party
episodes.overview: When Wendell's life falls apart from playing too much Puddin' Party, a cheesy, kids' phone game, Conor and the rest of the crew go to extreme lengths to break him of his lame obsession.

episodes.name: The Spirit Egg
episodes.overview: Connor and Wendell loose the school's Spirit Egg and assume the rival school stole it. The two infiltrate the rival school, only to find themselves trapped. Meanwhile, Franklin is chosen to take care of the Spirit Egg and he takes it too far.

episodes.name: The Sponsor
episodes.overview: The gang signs with a big video game company and are offered perks from a high-end corporate sponsor, but only if they replace Franklin as a team member.

episodes.name: The Driving Test
episodes.overview: Conor fails his driving test and ends up with an impossibly tough new driver's ed instructor.

episodes.name: The Psycho Zombie Bloodbath
episodes.overview: Conor gets his hands on a copy of the video game, "Psycho Zombie Bloodbath," which has recently been banned by the International Gaming Committee for being too creepy. After playing the game and staying up all night, Conor and the gang must battle real life zombies at their school.

episodes.name: The Incident
episodes.overview: Conor must overcome his demons by winning a dance competition with Ashley.

episodes.name: The Prank of the Century
episodes.overview: Conor and Ashley pull an amazing prank on Franklin while trying to win a contest.

episodes.name: The Odd Couple
episodes.overview: After Wendell saves him from a life-threatening accident, Conor feels indebted to his friend and allows Wendell to move in with him.

episodes.name: The Longest Yard
episodes.overview: Conor and Ashley give Mr. Spanks another chance at breaking the schoolâ€™s punting record in football while Wendell and Franklin compete to become the next school mascot.

episodes.name: The Penpal
episodes.overview: Conor goes undercover into the bizarre subculture of table-top, fantasy card games to help a fan who was wrongfully accused of a crime.

episodes.name: The Asteroid Blaster
episodes.overview: The gamers sneak off to use an asteroid-blasting simulator during a school field trip at a space lab.When a real asteroid begins hurdling towards the Earth, the gang must use their gaming skills to save the planet.

episodes.name: The Chillerz
episodes.overview: Conor and the gang take a product endorsement deal to try to dethrone their arch rival Lika from being the face of the gaming world.

episodes.name: The Cabin
episodes.overview: During a team-building retreat in the woods, the boys find themselves trapped without food or technology.

episodes.name: The Super Kart
episodes.overview: Franklin's ego drives him to lose a deluxe go-kart on loan from Funtendo to some kids from Mudd Valley High. Meanwhile, Wendell learns his cousin Dwayne is marrying his nemesis.

episodes.name: The Rock Band
episodes.overview: When the gang dazzles at the game "Rock Hero 5," Mr. Spanks encourages them to compete on the hit TV series "American Talent Factor."

episodes.name: The Goat
episodes.overview: It's a race against the clock when a goat that Conor is watching over escapes with a belly full of explosives.

episodes.name: The Escape Room
episodes.overview: Conor and the team participate in the latest gaming craze, an Escape Room. When the clues lead them to a large amount of cash, they inadvertently steal the money from a gang of crooks.

episodes.name: The Ringer
episodes.overview: Conor and Ashley recruit an NBA Player to be their ringer for a charity basketball game, and Wendell attempts to boost the popularity of his "Rekt" videos.

episodes.name: The Olym-pig Torch
episodes.overview: When Conor learns that the Olympic torch will pass through Redwood, he competes for the torchbearer title.

episodes.name: The Luchador
episodes.overview: Thumbs of Fury gets lost on their way to a tournament and wind up in Mexico where they instantly find themselves in trouble with the law.

episodes.name: The Rankening
episodes.overview: Conor and the gang find out where they rank in the International Gaming League Tournament

episodes.name: The ProtÃ©gÃ©
episodes.overview: After causing trouble for Janice, the gang is forced to volunteer for her Big Buddy program in which they are assigned little buddies for the week.

episodes.name: The Battle for Stump Hill
episodes.overview: With both Redwood and Yuba claiming they won the Battle of the Stump many years ago, the two rival towns instigate another battle to determine the winner once and for all.

episodes.name: The Prison Escape Movie
episodes.overview: The gamers enlist Janice's help to get into a highly anticipated action flick, but keeping her on board long enough to see the film proves far more difficult than they imagined.

episodes.name: The Long Weekend
episodes.overview: When the game rs get locked inside Mondale High during spring break with their least-favorite teacher, they must use their gaming skills to find a way out.

episodes.name: The Ghost
episodes.overview: When Ashley's late aunt leaves her a chest full of ghost-hunting equipment, Conor and Wendell see money-making potential and start their own medium business.

episodes.name: The Has-Been's Back
episodes.overview: Ashley is invited to a prestigious girls only tournament and the rest of the team joins her to show their support.

episodes.name: The DJs
episodes.overview: After Mr. Funkus is kicked out of his momâ€™s house, he moves into the school and teams up with Franklin to form a techno DJ duo.

episodes.name: The Detective
episodes.overview: When Franklin's literacy fair project is destroyed, Wendell is presumed to be the culprit and is expelled; Conor sets out to prove Wendell's innocence and clear his name.

episodes.name: The Arcade Hero
episodes.overview: After seemingly defeating a rare arcade game at Billy's, Wendell is rewarded a special gift from the game's creator, but Conor is the one who actually won the game.

episodes.name: The Stings
episodes.overview: After scoring early access to an exclusive gaming map for their next tourney, Thumbs of Fury discovers their scheming gaming nemesis has returned to Mondale High.

episodes.name: The Rodeo
episodes.overview: Conor and Wendell join a new Rodeo fitness regime in hopes they can get ranch-ripped and win a cash prize to cover the cost of the team's upcoming trip to IGL Nationals; Ashley helps Franklin with his prom-postal idea to win over Emma.
